#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:67
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Gentoo Linux can be installed using one of three <e>stage</e> tarball files.\n"
"A stage file is a tarball (compressed archive) that contains a minimal\n"
"environment.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:74
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"     A stage1 file contains nothing more than a compiler, Portage (Gentoo's\n"
"     software management system) and a couple of packages on which the compiler\n"
"     or Portage depends.\n"
"   "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:79
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"     A stage2 file contains a so-called bootstrapped system, a minimal\n"
"     environment from which one can start building all other necessary\n"
"     applications that make a Gentoo environment complete.\n"
"   "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:84
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"     A stage3 file contains a prebuilt minimal system which is almost fully\n"
"     deployable. It only lacks a few applications where you, the Gentoo user,\n"
"     needs to choose which one you want to install.\n"
"   "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:91
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"We will opt for a stage3 installation throughout this document. If you want to\n"
"perform a Gentoo installation using the stage1 or stage2 files, please use the\n"
"installation instructions in the <uri\n"
"link=\"/doc/en/handbook/handbook-alpha.xml\">Gentoo Handbook</uri>. They do\n"
"require a working Internet connection though.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:101
#, no-wrap
msgid "Gentoo Universal Installation CD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:105
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"An Installation CD is a bootable medium which contains a self-sustained Gentoo \n"
"environment. It allows you to boot Linux from the CD. During the boot process \n"
"your hardware is detected and the appropriate drivers are loaded. The Gentoo \n"
"Installation CDs are maintained by Gentoo developers.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:112
#, no-wrap
msgid "There currently are two Installation CDs available:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:117
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    The Universal Installation CD contains everything you need to install \n"
"    Gentoo. It provides stage3 files for common architectures, source code \n"
"    for the extra applications you need to choose from and, of course, the \n"
"    installation instructions for your architecture.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:123
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    The Minimal Installation CD contains only a minimal environment that allows \n"
"    you to boot up and configure your network so you can connect to the \n"
"    Internet. It does not contain any additional files and cannot be used \n"
"    during the current installation approach.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:131
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Gentoo also provides a Package CD. This is no Installation CD but an additional \n"
"resource that you can exploit during the installation of your Gentoo system. It\n"
"contains prebuilt packages (the so-called GRP set) that allows you to easily \n"
"and quickly install additional applications (such as OpenOffice.org, KDE, \n"
"GNOME, ...) immediately after the Gentoo installation and right before you \n"
"update your Portage tree.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:140
#, no-wrap
msgid "The use of the Package CD is covered later in this document. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><title>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:148
#, no-wrap
msgid "Download, Burn and Boot the Gentoo Universal Installation CD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:150
#, no-wrap
msgid "Downloading and Burning the Installation CD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:154
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can download the Universal Installation CD (and, if you want to, the \n"
"Packages CD as well) from one of our <uri \n"
"link=\"/main/en/mirrors.xml\">mirrors</uri>. The Installation CD is located in \n"
"the <path>releases/alpha/2005.0/installcd</path> directory;\n"
"the Package CD is located in the <path>releases/alpha/2005.0/packagecd</path>\n"
"directory.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:163
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Inside those directories you'll find so-called ISO-files. Those are full CD \n"
"images which you can write on a CD-R.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:168
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"After downloading the file, you can verify its integrity to see if it is \n"
"corrupted or not:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:174
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    You can check its MD5 checksum and compare it with the MD5 checksum we \n"
"    provide (for instance with the <c>md5sum</c> tool under Linux/Unix or \n"
"    <uri link=\"http://www.etree.org/md5com.html\">md5sum</uri> for Windows)\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:179
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    You can verify the cryptographic signature that we provide. You need to\n"
"    obtain the public key we use (17072058) before you proceed though.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:185
#, no-wrap
msgid "To fetch our public key using the GnuPG application, run the following command:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:188
#, no-wrap
msgid "Obtaining the public key"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:189
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ <i>gpg --keyserver pgp.mit.edu --recv-keys 17072058</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:193
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now verify the signature:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:196
#, no-wrap
msgid "Verify the cryptographic signature"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:197
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ <i>gpg --verify &lt;signature file&gt; &lt;downloaded iso&gt;</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:201
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To burn the downloaded ISO(s), you have to select raw-burning. How you\n"
"do this is highly program-dependent. We will discuss <c>cdrecord</c> and\n"
"<c>K3B</c> here; more information can be found in our <uri\n"
"link=\"/doc/en/faq.xml#isoburning\">Gentoo FAQ</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:209
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    With cdrecord, you simply type <c>cdrecord dev=/dev/hdc &lt;downloaded iso\n"
"    file&gt;</c> (replace <path>/dev/hdc</path> with your CD-RW drive's device\n"
"    path).\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:214
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    With K3B, select <c>Tools</c> &gt; <c>CD</c> &gt; <c>Burn Image</c>. Then\n"
"    you can locate your ISO file within the 'Image to Burn' area. Finally click\n"
"    <c>Start</c>.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:223
#, no-wrap
msgid "Booting the Universal Installation CD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:227
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When your Alpha is powered on, the first thing that gets started is the\n"
"firmware. It is loosely synonymous with the BIOS software on PC systems. There\n"
"are two types of firmware on Alpha systems: SRM (<e>Systems Reference \n"
"Manual</e>) and ARC (<e>Advanced Risc Console</e>).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:234
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"SRM is based on the Alpha Console Subsystem specification, which provides an\n"
"operating environment for OpenVMS, Tru64 UNIX, and Linux operating systems. ARC\n"
"is based on the Advanced RISC Computing (ARC) specification, which provides\n"
"an operating environment for Windows NT.  You can find a \n"
"<uri link=\"http://www.alphalinux.org/faq/SRM-HOWTO/\">detailed guide</uri> on \n"
"using SRM over at the Alpha Linux website.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:243
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If your Alpha system supports both SRC and ARCs (ARC, AlphaBIOS, ARCSBIOS) you\n"
"should follow <uri link=\"http://www.alphalinux.org/faq/x31.html\">these\n"
"instructions</uri> for switching to SRM. If your system already uses SRM, you\n"
"are all set. If your system can only use ARCs (Ruffian, nautilus, xl, etc.) you\n"
"will need to choose <c>MILO</c> later on when we are talking about bootloaders.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:251
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now to boot an Alpha Installation CD, put the CD-ROM in the tray and reboot the system.\n"
"You can use SRM to boot the Installation CD. If you cannot do that, you will have to use\n"
"<c>MILO</c>. If you don't have <c>MILO</c> installed already, use one of the\n"
"precompiled <c>MILO</c> images available on <uri\n"
"link=\"http://dev.gentoo.org/~taviso/milo/\">taviso's homepage</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:258
#, no-wrap
msgid "Booting a CD-ROM using SRM"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:259
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(List available hardware drives)</comment>\n"
"&gt;&gt;&gt; <i>show device</i>\n"
"dkb0.0.1.4.0        DKB0       TOSHIBA CDROM\n"
"<comment>(...)</comment>\n"
"<comment>(Substitute dkb0 with your CD-ROM drive device)</comment>\n"
"&gt;&gt;&gt; <i>boot dkb0 -flags 0</i>\n"
"<comment>To boot the 2.4 kernel instead of the default 2.6 kernel use:</comment>\n"
"&gt;&gt;&gt; <i>boot dkb -flags 1</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:269
#, no-wrap
msgid "Booting a CD-ROM using MILO"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:270
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(Substitute hdb with your CD-ROM drive device)</comment>\n"
"MILO&gt; <i>boot hdb:/boot/gentoo_2.6 initrd=/boot/gentoo_2_6.igz root=/dev/ram0 init=/linuxrc looptype=zisofs loop=/zisofs cdroot</i>\n"
"<comment>To boot the 2.4 kernel instead of the default 2.6 kernel use:</comment>\n"
"MILO&gt; <i>boot hdb:/boot/gentoo_2.4 initrd=/boot/gentoo_2_4.igz root=/dev/ram0 init=/linuxrc looptype=zisofs loop=/zisofs cdroot</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:277
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You should have a root (\"#\") prompt on the current console and can also switch\n"
"to other consoles by pressing Alt-F2, Alt-F3 and Alt-F4. Get back to the one you\n"
"started on by pressing Alt-F1.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:283
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now continue with <uri link=\"#hardware\">Extra Hardware Configuration</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:289
#, no-wrap
msgid "Extra Hardware Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:293
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When the Installation CD boots, it tries to detect all your hardware devices and\n"
"loads the appropriate kernel modules to support your hardware. In the\n"
"vast majority of cases, it does a very good job. However, in some cases (the\n"
"SPARC Installation CDs don't even do autodetection), it may not auto-load the kernel \n"
"modules you need. If the PCI auto-detection missed some of your system's \n"
"hardware, you will have to load the appropriate kernel modules manually. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:302
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In the next example we try to load the <c>8139too</c> module (support for \n"
"certain kinds of network interfaces):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:306
#, no-wrap
msgid "Loading kernel modules"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:307
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>modprobe 8139too</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:311
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you need PCMCIA support, you should start the <c>pcmcia</c> init script:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:314
#, no-wrap
msgid "Starting the PCMCIA init script"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:315
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>/etc/init.d/pcmcia start</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:321
#, no-wrap
msgid "Optional: Tweaking Hard Disk Performance"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:325
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you are an advanced user, you might want to tweak the IDE hard disk\n"
"performance using <c>hdparm</c>. With the <c>-tT</c> options you can\n"
"test the performance of your disk (execute it several times to get a\n"
"more precise impression):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:331
#, no-wrap
msgid "Testing disk performance"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:332
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>hdparm -tT /dev/hda</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:336
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To tweak, you can use any of the following examples (or experiment\n"
"yourself) which use <path>/dev/hda</path> as disk (substitute with your\n"
"disk):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:341
#, no-wrap
msgid "Tweaking hard disk performance"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:342
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>Activate DMA:</comment>                                       # <i>hdparm -d 1 /dev/hda</i>\n"
"<comment>Activate DMA + Safe Performance-enhancing Options:</comment>  # <i>hdparm -d 1 -A 1 -m 16 -u 1 -a 64 /dev/hda</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:349
#, no-wrap
msgid "Optional: User Accounts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:353
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you plan on giving other people access to your installation\n"
"environment or you want to chat using <c>irssi</c> without root privileges (for\n"
"security reasons), you need to create the necessary user accounts and change \n"
"the root password.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:360
#, no-wrap
msgid "To change the root password, use the <c>passwd</c> utility:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:363
#, no-wrap
msgid "Changing the root password"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:364
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>passwd</i>\n"
"New password: <comment>(Enter your new password)</comment>\n"
"Re-enter password: <comment>(Re-enter your password)</comment>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:370
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To create a user account, we first enter their credentials, followed by\n"
"its password. We use <c>useradd</c> and <c>passwd</c> for these tasks.\n"
"In the next example, we create a user called &quot;john&quot;.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:375
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating a user account"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:376
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>useradd -m -G users john</i>\n"
"# <i>passwd john</i>\n"
"New password: <comment>(Enter john's password)</comment>\n"
"Re-enter password: <comment>(Re-enter john's password)</comment>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:383
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can change your user id from root to the newly created user by using\n"
"<c>su</c>:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.0/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:387
#, no-wrap
msgid "Changing user id"
msgstr ""

